NoteADT - Class in utilities
This is the contract specification for a musical pitch or note.
NoteADT(double) - Constructor for class utilities.NoteADT
The constructors for a note accept a frequency as a double for Hz or a number of semitones as an int above or below the concert pitch (440Hz) or a music note as a String such as C#4 Imperfect frequencies are tuned to the nearest half pitch and if a frequency or semitones pushes the note midi value to greater than 127 and less than 0 the note midi values are set at 127 or 0 respectively.
